# Technology Stack Guardrails

Accepted ADRs are authoritative. Do not make ad-hoc framework/runtime/dependency
switches; confirm with the user before changing a baseline choice.

## Backend (`backend/`)

- Java 21 (compile `release 21`) + Spring Boot 3.x + Maven.
- PostgreSQL + Flyway + Spring Data JPA + QueryDSL. UUID PKs, UTC times, logical delete.
- Redis (Redisson): cache, distributed lock, idempotency. Kafka: async (at-least-once, retry + DLT).
- MinIO (Java SDK) object storage. LibreOffice headless for PDF. DOCX template engine for rendering.
- Spring Security + JWT; Argon2id hashing; fail-closed authorization.
- Jackson, MapStruct, Hibernate Validator, Resilience4j, Bucket4j, springdoc-openapi.
- Package layout: module-first under `com.bank.docgen.<module>`; rendering isolated from
  lifecycle/authorization/API-governance.

## Frontend (`frontend/`)

- Vue 3 + TypeScript + Vite + Element Plus + Pinia + Vue Router 4 + Axios.
- pnpm only (direct `pnpm` or shared resolver; never `corepack pnpm` in scripts).
- SCSS + CSS Modules; Vitest + Vue Test Utils + Playwright.

## API contract

- Match OpenAPI v1: unified envelope (`metadata`/`result`/`error`), error model
  (code + category + retryable + messageKey), enums in `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`, idempotency rules.

## Dependency policy

- Verify version availability in company-approved repositories first; stay within the
  accepted baseline. Quarantine of a version is normal governance, not a reason to switch stacks.
